text.tspan: HA: x not equal to a
These tests are called two-sided tests
Because we don't care whether x < a or
x > a - we only care if x = a.
For these tests, we have two regions where
x is definitely not near a, so we count the
area outside of both regions to get a p-value
If the p-value is less than 0.05
then we reject H0 and conclude that HA is more likely.
Here, the p-value is higher than 0.05, So we don't get to reject H0
